      "question": "Are interest-only loans risky?",
      "answer": "They can be riskier because the borrower may not reduce principal during the interest-only period, and the payment can rise later when principal repayment begins. Whether it is appropriate depends on the borrower’s strategy, reserves, and risk tolerance.",
